# CDK Project Conventions

## Commit messages (enforced by hook)
Format: `type(scope): short summary`
- `type`: feat | fix | docs | refactor | perf | test | chore | ci
- `scope`: lowercase kebab-case (e.g. `scheduler`, `paging`)
- `feat`, `fix`, `refactor` **must** include a body with implementation context
- Never use `WIP`, `tmp`, `fixup!`, or `squash!`

## Branch workflow
- Never push directly to `main` — always use a topic branch + PR
- Branch naming: `feat/<scope>`, `fix/<scope>`, `docs/<scope>`

## Module structure
Each subsystem lives in its own `src/<name>.rs`.  
Bare-metal-only code is gated with `#[cfg(target_os = "none")]`.  
Host-runnable code (tests, pure logic) has no cfg gate.

## no_std constraints
- No `std` imports anywhere in `src/` — use `core::` and `heapless`
- No dynamic allocation unless a `#[global_allocator]` is explicitly wired
- New dependencies must be `no_std`-compatible and added to the bare-metal `[target.'cfg(target_os = "none")'.dependencies]` section if hardware-specific
